t.au/news/2010-12-02/inside-a-brothel/2791456 \"Inside a brothel\"]\u2014interview by [[Richard Fidler]] with three brothel owners, June 2006 on [[ABC Local Radio]] (audio download available)\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20180807195258/http://www.france24.com/en/20141212-france-military-brothels-hidden-history-first-world-war-prostitution France's military brothels: Hidden history of the First World War]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Brothels| ]]\n[[Category:Sex industry]]\n", "name_user": "Shweta Stormborn", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eIndia", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brothel"}
{"title_page": "Living Proof (Camila Cabello song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 single by Camila Cabello}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Living Proof\n| cover    = \n| alt      = \n| type     = single\n| artist   = [[Camila Cabello]]\n| album    = [[Romance (Camila Cabello album)|Romance]]\n| released = {{Start date|2019|11|15}}\n| format   = \n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| genre    = [[Pop music|Pop]] \n| length   = {{duration|m=3|s=14}}\n| label    =\n* [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n* [[Syco Music|Syco]]\n| writer   = \n* [[Ali Tamposi]]\n* [[Camila Cabello]]\n* [[Justin Tranter]]\n* [[Mattman & Robin|Mattias Larsson]]\n* [[Mattman & Robin|Robin Fredriksson]]\n| producer   = [[Mattman & Robin]]\n| prev_title = [[Liar (Camila Cabello song)|Liar]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[My Oh My (Camila Cabello song)|My Oh My]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|6q4kCRREAgk|\"Living Proof\"}}|header=Music video}}\n}}\n\"'''Living Proof'''\" is a song by Cuban-American singer [[Camila Cabello]] from her second studio album ''[[Romance (Camila Cabello album)|Romance]]'' (2019), on which it appears as the second track. The song was released as the album's third single on November 15, 2019, along with the pre-order of the album.<ref name=\"Stereogum\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.stereogum.com/2065117/camila-cabello-living-proof/music/|title=Camila Cabello - \"Living Proof\"|date=November 15, 2019|website=[[Stereogum]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nCabello first teased the song in February 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iheartradio.ca/virginradio/london/news/listen-camila-cabello-shares-living-proof-1.10219554|title=LISTEN: Camila Cabello Shares 'Living Proof'|last=Kennedy|first=John R|website=iheartradio.ca|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref> She later announced the song's release on November 13, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B4zhUnZH0xR/|title=camila on Instagram: \"I can't believe this is happening. Romance. December 6. I just wanted this album to sound like what falling in love feels like, pretty...\"|via=[[Instagram]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref> Cabello has stated that the song is one of her favorites she wrote for ''[[Romance (Camila Cabello album)|Romance]]'', stating that it was \"her way of coping as a hopeless romantic\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/camila-cabello-drops-new-song-living-proof-one-of-her-favorite-tracks-from-upcoming-romance-album|title=Camila Cabello Drops New Song 'Living Proof' Off 'Romance' Album|website=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"UproxxArticle\">{{cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/pop/camila-cabello-living-proof-romance/|title=Camila Cabello Is Thankful For Her Crush On The Joyful Single 'Living Proof'|date=November 15, 2019|website=[[Uproxx]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Living Proof\" is a pop song that runs for 3 minutes and 14 seconds.<ref name=\"Stereogum\"/> The song opens with a clapping beat and a steady guitar.<ref name=\"UproxxArticle\"/> Cabello uses religious imagery to describe her relationship with her lover, in addition to a [[falsetto]] used \"in stomping and catchy chorus\".<ref name=\"UproxxArticle\"/><ref name=\"RS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/camila-cabello-living-proof-new-song-912586/|title=Camila Cabello Celebrates Healing Love on New Song 'Living Proof'|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|date=November 15, 2019|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref> The song's opening contains a sample of a recording by Andy Jones for his The Africa Heartwood Project, which contains orphans singing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.camilacabello.com/living-proof-the-africa-heartwood-project/|title=\"Living Proof\" - The Africa Heartwood Project|date=November 14, 2019|website=Camila Cabello|access-date=November 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe [[Alan Ferguson (director)|Alan Ferguson]]-directed music video was released on November 24, 2019, the night of her [[American Music Awards of 2019|American Music Awards]] performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8544598/camila-cabello-living-proof-video|title=Camila Cabello's 'Living Proof' Music Video Arrives Ahead of 2019 AMAs: Watch|last=Iasimone|first=Ashley|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 24, 2019|access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref> It was inspired by the [[John Everett Millais]] painting ''[[Ophelia (painting)|Ophelia]]'', which depicted the fictional [[William Shakespeare|Shakespearean]] [[Ophelia|character]] floating in a pool covered in flowers.<ref name=\"RS Video\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/camila-cabello-living-proof-video-917780/|title=Camila Cabello Drifts Like Ophelia in \u2018Living Proof\u2019 Video|last=Ehrlich|first=Brenna|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=November 24, 2019|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref> Throughout the video, she is seen frolicking with a group of dancers and laying in a bed of petals.<ref name=\"RS Video\"/> As of February 2020, it has over 15.7 million views and 440 thousand likes on [[YouTube]].\n\n==Live performances==\nCabello debuted the song at the [[American Music Awards of 2019|American Music Awards]], where she also performed \"[[Se\u00f1orita (Shawn Mendes and Camila Cabello song)|Se\u00f1orita]]\" alongside [[Shawn Mendes]] and \"[[Shake It Off]]\" alongside [[Taylor Swift]] and [[Halsey (singer)|Halsey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8544637/camila-cabello-living-proof-performance-2019-amas|title=Camila Cabello Brings Heaven and Hell to the 2019 American Music Awards With 'Living Proof' Performance|last=Hughes|first=Hilary|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 24, 2019|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref> On December 5, 2019 Cabello performed the song on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8545586/camila-cabello-living-proof-performance-fallon|title=Camila Cabello Opens Up About Her Pet Name For Shawn Mendes, Performs 'Living Proof' on 'Fallon'|author=Billboard Staff|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=December 6, 2019|access-date=December 7, 2019}}</ref> as well as on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' the next day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/camila-cabello-living-proof-ellen-degeneres-923227/|title=Camila Cabello Finds Salvation in Pink With \u2018Living Proof\u2019 Performance on \u2018Ellen\u2019|last=Blistein|first=Jon|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=December 6, 2019|access-date=December 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/122296864|title=Living Proof / Camila Cabello|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n* [[Camila Cabello]] \u2013 vocals, backing vocals, songwriting\n* [[Mattman & Robin]] \u2013 production, songwriting, instrumentation, backing vocals\n* [[Ali Tamposi]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Justin Tranter]] \u2013 songwriting\n* John Hanes \u2013 [[Audio engineer|engineering]]\n* Mattias Bylund \u2013 horn\n* Serben Ghenea \u2013 [[Audio mixing|mixing]]\n* Dustin Park \u2013 [[Audio engineer|recording]]\n* Ryan Dulude \u2013 recording\n* Peter Noos Johansson \u2013 trombone\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|84|artist=Camila Cabello|rowheader=true|accessdate=December 4, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Greece ([[IFPI Greece]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ifpi.gr/digital_iel.html|title=Greece Official IFPI Charts Digital Singles|work=IFPI Charts|accessdate=December 2, 2019|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200127125641/http://www.ifpi.gr/digital_ien.html|archive-date=January 27, 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| 82\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Ireland ([[Irish Recorded Music Association|IRMA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://irma.ie/index.cfm?page=irish-charts&chart=Singles|title=IRMA \u2013 Irish Charts|publisher=[[Irish Recorded Music Association]]|accessdate=November 23, 2019}}</ref>\n| 82\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Lithuania ([[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.agata.lt/lt/naujienos/savaites-klausomiausi-w47/|title=2019 47-os savait\u0117s klausomiausi (TOP 100)|language=Lithuanian|publisher=[[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]]|date=November 22, 2019|accessdate=November 29, 2019}}</ref>\n| 51\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Hot Singles ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4781|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=November 25, 2019|accessdate=November 22, 2019}}</ref>\n| 10\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| rowspan=\"2\"| November 15, 2019\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| {{hlist|[[Epic Records|Epic]]|[[Syco Music|Syco]]}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8543723/camila-cabello-living-proof|title=Camila Cabello Unveils New Song 'Living Proof': Stream It Now|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| {{hlist|Epic|[[Sony Music Australia]]}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://themusicnetwork.com/charts/issues/1263/1263-singles-to-radio/|title=Singles To Radio|website=The Music Network|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United Kingdom\n| December 6, 2019\n| {{hlist|Epic|Syco}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/3tqPdBWF9yMbTrfjWvfKV8t/radio-1-playlist|title=Radio 1 Playlist|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206192922/https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/3tqPdBWF9yMbTrfjWvfKV8t/radio-1-playlist|archivedate=December 6, 2019|website=[[BBC]]|access-date=December 6, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Camila Cabello}}\n\n[[Category:2019 singles]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:Camila Cabello songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Camila Cabello]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Ali Tamposi]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Robin Fredriksson]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Justin Tranter]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Mattman & Robin]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mattias Larsson]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 single by Camila Cabello}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Living Proof\n| cover    = \n| alt      = \n| type     = single\n| artist   = [[Camila Cabello]]\n| album    = [[Romance (Camila Cabello album)|Romance]]\n| released = {{Start date|2019|11|15}}\n| format   = \n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| genre    = [[Pop music|Pop]] \n| length   = {{duration|m=3|s=14}}\n| label    =\n* [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n* [[Syco Music|Syco]]\n| writer   = \n* [[Ali Tamposi]]\n* [[Camila Cabello]]\n* [[Justin Tranter]]\n* [[Mattman & Robin|Mattias Larsson]]\n* [[Mattman & Robin|Robin Fredriksson]]\n| producer   = [[Mattman & Robin]]\n| prev_title = [[Easy (Camila Cabello song)|Easy]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[My Oh My (Camila Cabello song)|My Oh My]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|6q4kCRREAgk|\"Living Proof\"}}|header=Music video}}\n}}\n\"'''Living Proof'''\" is a song by Cuban-American singer [[Camila Cabello]] from her second studio album ''[[Romance (Camila Cabello album)|Romance]]'' (2019), on which it appears as the second track. The song was released as the album's fifth single on November 15, 2019, along with the pre-order of the album.<ref name=\"Stereogum\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.stereogum.com/2065117/camila-cabello-living-proof/music/|title=Camila Cabello - \"Living Proof\"|date=November 15, 2019|website=[[Stereogum]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nCabello first teased the song in February 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iheartradio.ca/virginradio/london/news/listen-camila-cabello-shares-living-proof-1.10219554|title=LISTEN: Camila Cabello Shares 'Living Proof'|last=Kennedy|first=John R|website=iheartradio.ca|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref> She later announced the song's release on November 13, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B4zhUnZH0xR/|title=camila on Instagram: \"I can't believe this is happening. Romance. December 6. I just wanted this album to sound like what falling in love feels like, pretty...\"|via=[[Instagram]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref> Cabello has stated that the song is one of her favorites she wrote for ''[[Romance (Camila Cabello album)|Romance]]'', stating that it was \"her way of coping as a hopeless romantic\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/camila-cabello-drops-new-song-living-proof-one-of-her-favorite-tracks-from-upcoming-romance-album|title=Camila Cabello Drops New Song 'Living Proof' Off 'Romance' Album|website=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"UproxxArticle\">{{cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/pop/camila-cabello-living-proof-romance/|title=Camila Cabello Is Thankful For Her Crush On The Joyful Single 'Living Proof'|date=November 15, 2019|website=[[Uproxx]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Living Proof\" is a pop song that runs for 3 minutes and 14 seconds.<ref name=\"Stereogum\"/> The song opens with a clapping beat and a steady guitar.<ref name=\"UproxxArticle\"/> Cabello uses religious imagery to describe her relationship with her lover, in addition to a [[falsetto]] used \"in stomping and catchy chorus\".<ref name=\"UproxxArticle\"/><ref name=\"RS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/camila-cabello-living-proof-new-song-912586/|title=Camila Cabello Celebrates Healing Love on New Song 'Living Proof'|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|date=November 15, 2019|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref> The song's opening contains a sample of a recording by Andy Jones for his The Africa Heartwood Project, which contains orphans singing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.camilacabello.com/living-proof-the-africa-heartwood-project/|title=\"Living Proof\" - The Africa Heartwood Project|date=November 14, 2019|website=Camila Cabello|access-date=November 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe [[Alan Ferguson (director)|Alan Ferguson]]-directed music video was released on November 24, 2019, the night of her [[American Music Awards of 2019|American Music Awards]] performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8544598/camila-cabello-living-proof-video|title=Camila Cabello's 'Living Proof' Music Video Arrives Ahead of 2019 AMAs: Watch|last=Iasimone|first=Ashley|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 24, 2019|access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref> It was inspired by the [[John Everett Millais]] painting ''[[Ophelia (painting)|Ophelia]]'', which depicted the fictional [[William Shakespeare|Shakespearean]] [[Ophelia|character]] floating in a pool covered in flowers.<ref name=\"RS Video\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/camila-cabello-living-proof-video-917780/|title=Camila Cabello Drifts Like Ophelia in \u2018Living Proof\u2019 Video|last=Ehrlich|first=Brenna|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=November 24, 2019|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref> Throughout the video, she is seen frolicking with a group of dancers and laying in a bed of petals.<ref name=\"RS Video\"/> As of February 2020, it has over 15.7 million views and 440 thousand likes on [[YouTube]].\n\n==Live performances==\nCabello debuted the song at the [[American Music Awards of 2019|American Music Awards]], where she also performed \"[[Se\u00f1orita (Shawn Mendes and Camila Cabello song)|Se\u00f1orita]]\" alongside [[Shawn Mendes]] and \"[[Shake It Off]]\" alongside [[Taylor Swift]] and [[Halsey (singer)|Halsey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8544637/camila-cabello-living-proof-performance-2019-amas|title=Camila Cabello Brings Heaven and Hell to the 2019 American Music Awards With 'Living Proof' Performance|last=Hughes|first=Hilary|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 24, 2019|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref> On December 5, 2019 Cabello performed the song on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8545586/camila-cabello-living-proof-performance-fallon|title=Camila Cabello Opens Up About Her Pet Name For Shawn Mendes, Performs 'Living Proof' on 'Fallon'|author=Billboard Staff|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=December 6, 2019|access-date=December 7, 2019}}</ref> as well as on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' the next day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/camila-cabello-living-proof-ellen-degeneres-923227/|title=Camila Cabello Finds Salvation in Pink With \u2018Living Proof\u2019 Performance on \u2018Ellen\u2019|last=Blistein|first=Jon|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=December 6, 2019|access-date=December 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/122296864|title=Living Proof / Camila Cabello|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n* [[Camila Cabello]] \u2013 vocals, backing vocals, songwriting\n* [[Mattman & Robin]] \u2013 production, songwriting, instrumentation, backing vocals\n* [[Ali Tamposi]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Justin Tranter]] \u2013 songwriting\n* John Hanes \u2013 [[Audio engineer|engineering]]\n* Mattias Bylund \u2013 horn\n* Serben Ghenea \u2013 [[Audio mixing|mixing]]\n* Dustin Park \u2013 [[Audio engineer|recording]]\n* Ryan Dulude \u2013 recording\n* Peter Noos Johansson \u2013 trombone\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|84|artist=Camila Cabello|rowheader=true|accessdate=December 4, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Greece ([[IFPI Greece]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ifpi.gr/digital_iel.html|title=Greece Official IFPI Charts Digital Singles|work=IFPI Charts|accessdate=December 2, 2019|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200127125641/http://www.ifpi.gr/digital_ien.html|archive-date=January 27, 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| 82\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Ireland ([[Irish Recorded Music Association|IRMA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://irma.ie/index.cfm?page=irish-charts&chart=Singles|title=IRMA \u2013 Irish Charts|publisher=[[Irish Recorded Music Association]]|accessdate=November 23, 2019}}</ref>\n| 82\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Lithuania ([[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.agata.lt/lt/naujienos/savaites-klausomiausi-w47/|title=2019 47-os savait\u0117s klausomiausi (TOP 100)|language=Lithuanian|publisher=[[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]]|date=November 22, 2019|accessdate=November 29, 2019}}</ref>\n| 51\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Hot Singles ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4781|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=November 25, 2019|accessdate=November 22, 2019}}</ref>\n| 10\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n